Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Spray insides of 4 ovenproof 2-cup soup bowls with CRISCO(R) Original No-Stick Cooking Spray.** Set aside. In food processor bowl with metal blade or blender, place all vinaigrette ingredients except oil. Cover; process until smooth. With food processor running, slowly pour oil through feed tube until mixture is thickened. Set aside. Spray 1 side of each tortilla with CRISCO(R) Original No-Stick Cooking Spray. Sprinkle cumin and 1/2 teaspoon salt evenly over sprayed sides of tortillas. Press tortillas, seasoned sides up, in bowls. Place bowls in 15x10x1-inch pan. Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Remove tortillas from bowls; place upside down on cooling rack. Cool completely. In large bowl, mix chicken and 1 1/3 cups mango. In small bowl, mix 1 tablespoon lime juice and the avocado. Add avocado and remaining salad ingredients to chicken mixture; mix well. Add vinaigrette; mix well. To serve, spoon chicken salad into tortilla bowls. (Bowls will be full.) Serve immediately.